Two fair six-sided dice are rolled. Let \(A\) be event that the first die is 3, let \(B\) be the event that the second die is 4, and let \(C\) be the event that their sum is 7. Which of the following are true?

[x] \(A\) is independent of \(B\).
[x] \(A\) is independent of \(C\).
[x] \(A\), \(B\) and \(C\) are pair-wise independent.
[ ] \(A\), \(B\) and \(C\) are mutually independent.